h vocalist and composer [[Tarja Turunen]]. The record was released on 30 August 2019.\n\n==Background==\nOn ''In the Raw'', released on August 30th 2019, composer and vocalist Tarja Turunen joined forces with other Heavy Metal vocalists such as [[Bj\u00f6rn Strid]], [[Tommy Karevik]], and [[Cristina Scabbia]], thus including in the album vocal colaborations with them.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tarjaturunen.com/albums-in-the-raw/|title=In The Raw|accessdate=April 11,2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 September 2019, Tarja Turunen started the \"Raw Tour\" to promote \"In the Raw\" album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tarjaturunen.com/past-events-raw-tour-2019-20/|title=Past Event|accessdate=April 11,2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nIn the Raw has been widely acclaimed by both heavy metal fans and music critics in general, as Gary Hernandez from \"Metal Temple\" wrote: \"\u201cIn the Raw\u201d reminds us how good Symphonic Metal can be: Vocal performances executed to perfection, versatile songwriting, thoughtful arrangements, deeply talented musicians, excellent production values\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metal-temple.com/site/catalogues/entry/reviews/cd_3/t_2/tarja-in-the-raw.htm|title= Tarja - In The Raw: '\u201cIn the Raw\u201d review|accessdate=4-11-2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n\n {{Track listing\n| total_length = \n| title1 = Dead Promises\n| note1 = featuring [[Bj\u00f6rn Strid]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Tarja Turunen]]|[[Alex Scholpp]]}}\n| length1 = 5:50\n| title2 = Goodbye Stranger\n| note2 = featuring [[Christina Scabbia]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Turunen|Scholpp}}\n| length2 = 5:12\n| title3 = Tears in Rain\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Turunen|Johnny Lee Andrews}}\n| length3 = 4:28\n| title4 = Rail Roads\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Turunen|Erik Nyholm}}\n| length4 = 4:00\n| title5 = You and I\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Turunen|Michael Zlanabitnig|Mathias Lindblom}}\n| length5 = 4:07\n| title6 = The Golden Chamber (Awaken - Loputon Yo - Alchemy)\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Turunen|Jim Michael Doole